The paper discusses neural networks and their ability to learn through synaptic plasticity, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the optimization of cost functions, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of structured feedforward, lateral, and feedback connections suggests that the paper may also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the credit assignment problem, which is a common issue in control systems (cs.SY).
